1. Configure Git (First Time Only)

Check your Git version:

git --version

Set your name:

git config --global user.name "Your Name"

Set your email:

git config --global user.email "you@example.com"

View all settings:

git config --list
2. Create a Repository

Initialize a new Git repository:

git init

Clone an existing repository:

git clone <repository-url>

Example:

git clone https://github.com/username/project.git
3. Check Status

See what has changed:

git status
4. Stage Changes

Stage one file:

git add index.html

Stage all changes:

git add .

Stage everything:

git add --all
5. Commit Changes

Commit staged changes:

git commit -m "Add navbar"

Commit tracked changes (not new files):

git commit -a -m "Fix navbar"
6. View History

Show commit history:

git log

Short version:

git log --oneline

Graph view:

git log --oneline --graph --all
7. Branches

List branches:

git branch

Create a branch:

git branch feature/navbar

Create and switch:

git switch -c feature/navbar

or

git checkout -b feature/navbar

Delete a branch:

git branch -d feature/navbar

Force delete:

git branch -D feature/navbar
8. Switch Branches

Modern command:

git switch main

Older command:

git checkout main
9. Merge

Merge a branch into the current branch:

git merge feature/navbar
10. Push to GitHub

First push of a new branch:

git push -u origin feature/navbar

Later pushes:

git push

Push main:

git push origin main
11. Pull Changes

Download and merge changes:

git pull

Pull from a specific branch:

git pull origin main
12. Fetch

Download changes without merging:

git fetch
13. Remote Repositories

View remotes:

git remote -v

Add a remote:

git remote add origin <repository-url>

Change the remote URL:

git remote set-url origin <new-url>

Remove a remote:

git remote remove origin
14. Differences

See unstaged changes:

git diff

See staged changes:

git diff --staged
15. Undo Changes

Discard changes in one file:

git restore index.html

Unstage a file:

git restore --staged index.html

Restore all files:

git restore .
16. Remove Files

Remove from Git and disk:

git rm file.txt

Rename a file:

git mv old.html new.html
17. Stash

Temporarily save work:

git stash

View stashes:

git stash list

Restore the latest stash:

git stash pop
18. Tags

Create a tag:

git tag v1.0

Push tags:

git push --tags
19. Reset

Soft reset:

git reset --soft HEAD~1

Mixed reset:

git reset HEAD~1

Hard reset (⚠️ deletes local changes):

git reset --hard HEAD~1
20. Revert

Undo a commit without rewriting history:

git revert <commit-hash>
21. Clean

Remove untracked files:

git clean -f

Remove untracked files and folders:

git clean -fd
22. Inspect

Show current branch:

git branch --show-current

Show a commit:

git show
23. Helpful Everyday Workflow
git status
git pull origin main
git switch -c feature/about
git add .
git commit -m "Add About section"
git push -u origin feature/about

Then open a Pull Request on GitHub.

24. Team Collaboration Workflow
main
│
├── feature/navbar
├── feature/hero
├── feature/about
├── feature/contact

Each teammate:

Pulls the latest main.
Creates a feature branch.
Commits changes.
Pushes the branch.
Opens a Pull Request.
Merges into main after review.
